Incumbent governor and candidate of the All Progressives Congress, APC  in Saturday’s governorship election in Kogi state, Yahaya Bello has been announced as the winner of Ijumu local government area. Bello polled a total of 11,425 votes against the 7,587 votes recorded by the candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, Engr. Musa Wada, as announced by the Independent National Electoral Commission. READ: #KogiDecides: INEC announces official results – LIVE BLOG Natasha Akpoti of the Social Democratic Party, SDP scored 223 votes. Total registered voters: 59,578
